From: Sean Young <sean@mess.org>
Date: Sun, 19 May 2019 15:28:22 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] media: au0828: fix null dereference in error path
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.2.6
Git-commit: 6d0d1ff9ff21fbb06b867c13a1d41ce8ddcd8230

commit 6d0d1ff9ff21fbb06b867c13a1d41ce8ddcd8230 upstream.

au0828_usb_disconnect() gets the au0828_dev struct via usb_get_intfdata,
so it needs to set up for the error paths.

Reported-by: syzbot+357d86bcb4cca1a2f572@syzkaller.appspotmail.com
Signed-off-by: Sean Young <sean@mess.org>
Signed-off-by: Mauro Carvalho Chehab <mchehab+samsung@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/media/usb/au0828/au0828-core.c | 12 ++++++------
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/usb/au0828/au0828-core.c b/drivers/media/usb/au0828/au0828-core.c
index f746f6e2f686..a8a72d5fbd12 100644
--- a/drivers/media/usb/au0828/au0828-core.c
+++ b/drivers/media/usb/au0828/au0828-core.c
@@ -719,6 +719,12 @@ static int au0828_usb_probe(struct usb_interface *interface,
 	/* Setup */
 	au0828_card_setup(dev);
 
+	/*
+	 * Store the pointer to the au0828_dev so it can be accessed in
+	 * au0828_usb_disconnect
+	 */
+	usb_set_intfdata(interface, dev);
+
 	/* Analog TV */
 	retval = au0828_analog_register(dev, interface);
 	if (retval) {
@@ -737,12 +743,6 @@ static int au0828_usb_probe(struct usb_interface *interface,
 	/* Remote controller */
 	au0828_rc_register(dev);
 
-	/*
-	 * Store the pointer to the au0828_dev so it can be accessed in
-	 * au0828_usb_disconnect
-	 */
-	usb_set_intfdata(interface, dev);
-
 	pr_info("Registered device AU0828 [%s]\n",
 		dev->board.name == NULL ? "Unset" : dev->board.name);
 
